<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

	<PropertyGroup>
		<!-- Build & Lang -->
		<Nullable>enable</Nullable>
		<IsPackable>true</IsPackable>
		<OutputType>Library</OutputType>
		<IsTrimmable>false</IsTrimmable>
		<Deterministic>true</Deterministic>
		<AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
		<TargetFramework>netstandard2.1;net10.0</TargetFramework>

		<TrimMode>partial</TrimMode>
		<PublishAot>true</PublishAot>

		<Description><![CDATA[
Nalix.Abstractions defines the fundamental abstractions, enums, and shared contracts for the Nalix ecosystem. It provides base interfaces, environment helpers, serialization primitives, and protocol definitions used across all Nalix modules.

This library focuses on performance, consistency, and cross-platform reliability — serving as the foundation for higher-level components such as Nalix.Framework, Nalix.Network, Nalix.SDK, Nalix.Shared, and Nalix.Logging.
		]]></Description>

		<PackageReleaseNotes><![CDATA[
- Foundational Abstractions: Core interfaces for connection lifecycles and shared framework contracts used across all Nalix modules.
- Networking Standards: Unified IPacket, IBufferLease, and protocol enums (CipherSuite, Snowflake) for consistent communication.
- Memory & Concurrency: High-performance gating and memory-leasing primitives designed for low-allocation networking scenarios.
- System Diagnostics: Flexible exception models and logging abstractions providing the base for framework-wide observability.
		]]></PackageReleaseNotes>
    </PropertyGroup>

    <Import Project="..\Nalix.Build.props" />
    <Import Project="..\Package.Build.props" />
	
    <ItemGroup>
		<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.Logging.Abstractions" Version="10.0.5" />
    </ItemGroup>
	
</Project>
